defaultQuestion number
defaultQuestion posed by 
defaultThe Transport 
defaultCommittee
defaultAnswers submitted by the West Sussex Cycle Forum
default1
defaultWhat is the rationale for the Government’s proposals to devolve to a local level decision-making on transport expenditure? 
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;
defaultWhat are the advantages and disadvantages of the Government’s 
defaultapproach? Are there better models?
defaultThere are a number of disadvantages 
defaultassociated with
default devolved decision-making in West Sussex:
default&#xa0;
defaultExpectations
default have been raised that local decision-making would direct money more effectively to the needs of cyclists, but as the rest of this response demonstrates, the 
defaultimplementation in West Sussex has largely dashed those expectations.
default&#xa0;
defaultDevolving transport decision
defaults makes it almost impossible to plan and deliver non-local transport infrastructure, even on the scale of inter-urban 
defaultcycleways
default between 
defaultneighbouring
default towns [
defaultsee 
default1].
default&#xa0;
default Transport is by its nature a very network-oriented issue, so changes in one location can ha
defaultve big impacts on another location: but 
defaultlocalised
default transport spending doesn't allow this to be taken into account at all [
defaultsee 
default2]. Transport-specific planning and design knowledge is lost, as local councils do not have the expertise and experience in transpo
defaultrt planning matters [
defaultsee 
default3].
default&#xa0;
defaultExamples - 
default[1] A county 
defaultcouncillor
default from Lancing would like to build a 
defaultcycleway
default between Lancing and 
defaultWorthing
default, to benefit Lancing residents. However most of the 
defaultcycleway
default will be within 
defaultWorthing's
default boundary, so he has to persuade 
defaulta 
defaultWorthing
default 
defaultcouncillor
default to promote his 
defaultcycleway
default, even though it has much less value to 
defaultWorthing
default residents. This means that it's unlikely to ever happen; even though there is local community need and desire.
default&gt; [2] The A27 through 
defaultWorthing
default is likely to become 
defaultsignificantly more congested when the improvements at 
defaultHandcross
default Hill on the A23 are completed, making it much easier to drive to the south coast from Gatwick and further north. If the Arundel bypass 
defaultwere ever to be
default built, 
defaultit
default would lead to significant incre
defaultases in congestion in 
defaultWorthing
default from traffic finding it easier to drive along the A27 to and from the west. The A27 at Southampton is significantly more congested since the M3 
defaultTwyford
default Down cutting opened.
default&gt; [3] Local officials recently placed a sharp-edged 
defaultdark-blue sculpture in the middle of National Cycle Network Route 2 
defaultcycleway
default in Lancing. The local officers involved were unaware of the importance of this route, or the number of people on bicycles using it daily to commute to and from work. One officer w
defaultas even unaware that the cycle route was continuous to 
defaultWorthing
default, even though it had been so for some years!
